items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Bonesaw Cycling Collective group ride. Instagram.

Last Tuesday of every month. Meet at 6:45 pm, roll at 7 pm.

Start: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge. Finish: Sabo Bridge

Distance: typically 10-15 miles. Pace: typically 10 mph. 

This is a no-drop ride with a good mix between party pace and whistling pace and we will stay together with a dedicated leader and sweep.

Please bring all necessary supplies recommended for riding - layers, helmet, lock, emergency tools, tubes, snacks, etc. in case of emergency.
items.location: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

Group ride (no-drop) EZ Bike Club Monthly Ride. Instagram.

6:30 pm social meet, 7:15pm roll out.

First Tuesday of every month through October.

Start: 1301 Theodore Wirth Parkway

Distance: Typically 10-15 miles. Pace: Chill pace, nobody left behind (likely 10-12 mph). 

Open to all. Bring lights. This ride is all about unity and movement, celebrating people of color on bikes, community connection, and the power of the outdoors in connection to our physical and mental well-being.

items.description:
Bike Polo (pick-up game) Bike Polo New Player Mondays. Facebook.

Monday’s 5pm - dark all summer long (weather permitting).

Location: Minneapolis Bike Polo Court (E 35th St and 3rd Ave S)

Looking to try out bike polo? Bring your bike, helmet (light gloves are nice). All skill levels welcome! 

We will have some mallets and balls for you to practice shooting the ball around and other skills.
items.location: Minneapolis Bike Polo Court, 3429 3rd Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55408, USA

items.summary: BWB Monthly Sunday rides, Women only
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Biking with Baddies Monthly Sunday rides, Women only Instagram, Website.

Last Sunday of every month. 2:00 PM 

Start: Logan Park 690 13th Ave NE

Who is this for: Women only

“All levels welcomed, no one left behind. Always refer to the website for updates. Come out with your bike and make new friends. There may be people you know, and/or folks that might want to get to know you on this ride. Even if that’s not the goal, come outside to cycle with us in nature.”
items.location: Logan Park, Minneapolis, MN, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Wedge Live Emergency Bike Ride. Event page.

When: Every Sunday at 7pm. Roll at 7:30pm. Aug 24, 2025, Aug 31, 2025

Start: Mueller Park (Colfax and W 25th St)

Distance: ?. Pace: Conversational, likely 8-12 mph.

What is an emergency bike ride? It's an immediate, systematic, coordinated response among partners at all levels, to the community's need for more bike rides.

Who can participate? Anyone of any skill level who feels an urgent need to ride your bike at a leisurely conversational pace in a group setting.

Are scooters ok? Yes.
items.location: Mueller Park, 2509 Colfax Ave South, Minneapolis, MN 55405, USA

items.description:
Group ride (drop) Tuesday Night Rides. Facebook.

When: Tuesdays. Meet at 5:45 pm, roll at 6:00 pm. Aug 19, 2025, Aug 26, 2025

Start and Finish: HeadFlyer Brewing

Two pace groups. Spicy: 14-16 mph pace for 20-25 miles Mild: 11-13 mph pace for 15-20 miles.

Routes published on Monday in the FB group. Rides feature a mid-ride restaurant stop and have the option to end back at Headflyer for a pint. There are no sweeps, so this can be a drop ride. Bring lights, lock, helmet, flat-fixing kit, anything you need to get yourself home.
items.location: HeadFlyer Brewing, 861 E Hennepin Ave #100, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA

Group ride (drop) Tuesday Night Rides. Facebook.

When: Tuesdays. Meet at 5:45 pm, roll at 6:00 pm. Aug 19, 2025, Aug 26, 2025

Start and Finish: HeadFlyer Brewing

Two pace groups. Spicy: 14-16 mph pace for 20-25 miles Mild: 11-13 mph pace for 15-20 miles.

Group ride (no-drop) Perennial Family Fun Rides Instagram. Website.

Third Saturday in June, July, August, and September

Jun 21, 2025, Jul 19, 2025, Aug 16, 2025, Sep 20, 2025

All rides will meet at 9:30am and roll out at 10am. NOT ALL rides will meet at Perennial Cycle so watch out on our socials for more info leading up to each ride.

Come enjoy morning rides accompanied by singalongs, story-time, face-painting, treats, and more!

Race (CX) Versus cross III. Instagram

When: Sunday Oct 19, 2025. 9am-4pm

Where: Huset Park, Columbia Heights. 

Cost: TBA (reg opens Sept 1), but typically $25-35/race, with a $10 “citizen” race for people new to the sport.

The best cyclocross race in Minnesota is back for its third year! Come race and spectate at Huset Park in Columbia Heights. Get some food from @kramarczuks and @nordicdogs612, chat all things bike fit, strength programming and PT with @go_physio_mn, and hang with our other vendors and sponsors! There will be a kids race and face painting—stick around for our signature Tracklocross race and raffle at the end of the day! Registration Opens September 1—stay tuned!
items.location: Huset Park, 3965 Jefferson St NE, Columbia Heights, MN 55421, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) MCF Tu Night CX. Instagram. Website.

Start: Aquila Park (St. Louis Park)

Cost: All Races are $25, adding a second race is $5. (Some weeks, racing may be free if you volunteer for set-up or teardown. Check with MCF for details) 

All categories are self-selected and non gender-specific, so use your best judgement.

5:30 PM - Beginners & Juniors - (30 minutes)

6:10 PM - Intermediate & Masters (40+) - (40 minutes)

7:00 PM - Advanced - (50 minutes)

Check MCF instagram or website for more details. These are unsanctioned races, so you don’t need a racing license. No Gods, No USAC.

CX is a volunteer-intensive sport and we need all of the setup and tear down help we can get. Nights 6 and 7 will only be possible if we have sufficient crew to staff them. If you or your team are interested in volunteering please email calendarcoordinator@mncyclingfederation.org!
items.location: Aquila Park, 3110 Xylon Ave S, St Louis Park, MN 55426, USA

items.description:
Gathering MBMA Podium Party. Instagram.

Friday Sep 26, 2025. 5-10pm.

Start: 801 Transfer Road Bay #9

The Summer Series is wrapped and we’re celebrating big.

🍔 Food + drinks (we’ll do our best to accommodate dietary needs)

🎶 Music + vibes

🚲 $1 mini-games (winner takes the pot)

Huge thank you to our volunteers and sponsors for making this all possible and thank you to everyone who came out and raced — it was a good time all season long.

We’ll also be crowning our Summer Series Champions 🏆 in Open, Trans/GNC, Women, First Fixed, and DFL. This one’s for the whole community — everyone pull up, kick it, and vibe together as we close out the season.

items.description:
Self-supported ride Taco Bell Century Instagram. Route link.

Saturday Sep 20, 2025 8:00 AM. Roll at 8:30 AM.

Start: 1540 Stinson Boulevard Northeast (Taco Bell by the Quarry)

Get Baja blasted with your friends again! The third annual Taco Bell Century by Corpsewhale Racing.

A route will be provided when we get closer to the date. I promise more Taco Bells than is reasonable. We'll do a loop and there's plenty of parking spots in the Quarry lots for riders who drive to the start.

Fuel only with Taco Bell, or don't, we're not cops. The goal is fun. Ride at your own pace, we won't stick together as a group. You are responsible for yourself.

Location: Whitetail trailhead, Riverfalls, WI. Map link.

Who’s this for: “MDL hosts events specifically for marginalized genders. FTW / anyone but cis-men are welcome at our rides! Here’s a great resource defining FTW from our friends at GreaseRag.”

Come closeout the season with us at Whitetail!  Sure to see some amazing fall colors meet at the trailhead to learn names and get started. 

OPEN GROUP RIDES: All skill levels welcome and we will break into groups as necessary so we all have a fun ride! 

This is a no drop ride so plan for plenty of time to stop and chat, scope out features, and generally bring the stoke!  We will head over to the nearby brewery for after ride snacks and pals!
